-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.2","title":"Safety invariants and non-goals for br sync","description":"Define a precise, testable set of invariants for br sync. Examples: (1) No git commands executed. (2) No file creation/deletion outside .beads. (3) JSONL export uses atomic write/rename and never truncates on failure. (4) Import refuses conflict markers and validates schema/prefix. (5) Any operation that could discard data requires explicit --force. Also document explicit non-goals (no auto commit, no hooks, no daemon).","acceptance_criteria":"- Invariants list is explicit and testable\n- Non-goals are clearly stated\n- Invariants are traceable to guardrails and tests","notes":"These invariants drive implementation and tests. Phrase them so they can be directly asserted.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:03:44.608543467-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:03:44.608543467-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.2","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:03:44.610005188-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.2","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:35.430762171-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
