-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","title":"Implement path allowlist and canonicalization for sync IO","description":"Add a centralized path-validation helper that enforces: sync IO paths must reside under the active .beads directory (or an explicitly allowed JSONL path), must not escape via .. or symlinks, and must never target repository source files. The helper should be used by both export and import.","acceptance_criteria":"- Path validation helper exists and is used in sync export/import\n- Attempts to use paths outside .beads fail fast with clear errors\n- Symlink and traversal edge cases are handled","notes":"This is the primary guardrail against overbroad path operations. Use canonicalized paths and explicit allowlist checks.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:00.545619633-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:00.545619633-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:00.547737047-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.42323102-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:39.850049204-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.2","title":"Make JSONL export atomic and failure-safe","description":"Ensure export writes to a temp file in the same directory, fsyncs, and atomically renames into place. Never truncate or overwrite the existing JSONL on failure. Preserve file permissions where possible.","acceptance_criteria":"- Export uses write-to-temp + fsync + atomic rename\n- Existing JSONL is preserved on failure\n- Errors are explicit and do not modify unrelated files","notes":"Atomic export prevents partial writes and data loss, and helps avoid the class of bugs that can delete or blank files.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:04.858265362-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:04.858265362-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.2","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:04.859911339-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.2","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.474522448-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.2","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.523650556-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.3","title":"Harden JSONL import safety checks","description":"Strengthen import guardrails: detect conflict markers, validate JSON schema per line, enforce prefix and metadata checks, and require explicit --force for any operation that could discard or override data. Import must never delete repository files or touch paths outside .beads.","acceptance_criteria":"- Conflict markers abort import with clear error\n- Prefix/schema validation enforced by default\n- Risky overrides require explicit --force\n- No filesystem side effects outside allowed paths","notes":"Import is a major risk surface because it can overwrite DB state. Guardrails must be strict and explicit.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:10.391899706-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:10.391899706-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.3","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:10.393222575-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.3","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.575557402-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.3","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.625533175-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.4","title":"Guarantee no git operations are executed by br sync","description":"Audit sync code paths to ensure br never executes git commands or triggers hooks. Add a hard guard (feature flag, runtime assertion, or dependency inversion) that prevents any git invocation from sync paths.","acceptance_criteria":"- No git execution in sync path (verified by audit)\n- Hard guard prevents future git integration in sync\n- Error messaging makes the non-goal explicit","notes":"The incident class involved sync creating commits. br must never perform git operations by design and by enforcement.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:15.270419197-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:15.270419197-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.4","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:15.271842305-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.4","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.676895146-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.4","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.726685179-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.5","title":"Add explicit guards against filesystem deletion outside .beads","description":"Ensure sync never deletes any filesystem content outside the allowed .beads paths. If deletion is ever needed (e.g., temp file cleanup), it must be scoped and validated. Add a centralized guard that rejects any delete/overwrite targeting repo source files.","acceptance_criteria":"- Delete/overwrite operations are scoped to allowed paths\n- Any attempt to target other paths fails fast\n- Guard is reused across sync components","notes":"Even temporary cleanup can be dangerous if paths are wrong. Make deletion impossible outside the allowed scope.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:21.54983608-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:21.54983608-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.5","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:21.551839409-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.5","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.778462162-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.6","title":"Add sync safety checks to br doctor","description":"Extend br doctor to validate sync safety preconditions: JSONL path within .beads, no merge conflict markers, metadata consistency, and absence of unsafe config. Provide clear guidance if checks fail.","acceptance_criteria":"- Doctor reports unsafe JSONL paths and conflict markers\n- Doctor offers actionable remediation steps\n- Checks are read-only","notes":"Doctor is the safe entry point for users; it should prevent risky sync operations before they run.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:26.679333733-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:26.679333733-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.6","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:04:26.68067653-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.6","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.827597273-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.6","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:05:42.879567148-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.7","title":"Add sync preflight stage with explicit safety checks","description":"Introduce a preflight step for sync that validates workspace state (beads dir exists, JSONL path safe, metadata consistent, no conflict markers if importing) before any writes occur. Preflight must be read-only and fail-fast.","acceptance_criteria":"- Preflight runs before export/import\n- Preflight is read-only and fail-fast\n- Preflight errors are actionable","notes":"Preflight reduces the risk of partial operations and makes the safety model explicit.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:14.416975074-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:14.416975074-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.7","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:14.418964979-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.7","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:39.697459506-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.7","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:39.750990328-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.8","title":"Define and enforce explicit allowlist of sync-touched files","description":"Enumerate the exact files br sync is allowed to touch (e.g., .beads/issues.jsonl, .beads/metadata.json, .beads/.manifest.json, temp files in .beads). Enforce this allowlist in code and tests.","acceptance_criteria":"- Allowlist is explicit and documented\n- Sync refuses to touch files outside the allowlist\n- Tests cover allowlist enforcement","notes":"This makes the safety boundary concrete and auditable. Any expansion requires deliberate review.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:20.225436859-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:20.225436859-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.8","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:20.226785978-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.2.8","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:06:39.800984856-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
-{"id":"beads_rust-0v1.3","title":"Safety test suite and regression coverage for sync","description":"Build a rigorous test suite that proves sync cannot modify repository source files, cannot invoke git, and is atomic/failure-safe. Include regression cases based on the incident class.","acceptance_criteria":"- Unit tests for path guards and conflict detection\n- Integration tests that snapshot file trees and verify only JSONL is touched\n- Regression test for the 'sync deletes code' failure class","notes":"Tests are the non-negotiable guardrails. Include unit, integration, and end-to-end scenarios that simulate real repos.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:03:23.753646355-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:03:23.753646355-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-0v1.3","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-0v1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:03:23.755023316-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
